<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-03T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-03T18:00:00-05:00" n="16" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d16">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114/2885</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-03T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 3, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>988. Your 1650, September 15, noon. Department is of the opinion that
                            limit of 1,000 parcels transported by each steamer of the French Line
                            will for the present be an ample allowance and that no steps need yet be
                            taken to ship by other means the number of parcels in excess of quantity
                            named.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>